.TH holbertonschool printf

.SH NAME
.BR _printf

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR "printf()"
 is an output function from the standard library of the C programming language and other programming languages. This function allows you to display information on the screen or write it to a file.

The basic syntax of the printf function is as follows:

printf(format, arg1, arg2, ...);

"format" is a string that specifies the formatting of the output, while "arg1", "arg2", ... are optional arguments that are inserted into the formatting string.
.SH EXAMPLES
Here is a simple example that uses the printf function to display a string

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
   char c = 'A';
   printf("The character is: %c\n", c);
   return 0;
}


.SH CONVERSION

        %c \- is to print a charecter

        %s \- is to print a string
 	
	%d \- is to print a decimal

        %i \- is to print a integer


